  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Malcesine is perfect if you’re looking for a summer holiday right on the lake.</p>
<h2>Panoramic views of Lake Garda</h2>
<p>We love sitting on the terrace and enjoying the panoramic views over <a data-udi="umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473}" title="Lake Garda">Lake Garda</a> with a glass of prosecco. There’s a sunbathing terrace with equally good views – grab a lounger and relax for the whole day.</p>
<h2>Central location in Malcesine</h2>
<p>The hotels' location can’t be beaten. It’s right in the centre of Malcesine with the ferry port on its doorstep. Take some day trips to towns like <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/italy/lake-garda/sirmione" title="Sirmione">Sirmione</a>, <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/italy/lake-garda/garda" title="Garda">Garda</a> and <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/italy/lake-garda/limone" title="Limone">Limone</a> and make sure you spend some time in <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/italy/lake-garda/malcesine" title="Malcesine">Malcesine</a> itself. The Monte Baldo cable car is just a short walk from the hotel and the views and walking opprtunities from the top are fantastic.</p>]]></description>
